#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.58"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.58:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.58:0.2"
msgid "6. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "6. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.58:0.3"
msgid "58. Āsavasutta"
msgstr "58. Defilements"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Chahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo "
"dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant with six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated "
"to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy "
"of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the "
"world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:2.1"
msgid "Katamehi chahi?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "an6.58:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno ye āsavā saṃvarā pahātabbā te saṃvarena pahīnā "
"honti, "
msgstr ""
"It’s a mendicant who, by restraint, has given up the defilements that should "
"be given up by restraint. "

msgctxt "an6.58:2.3"
msgid "ye āsavā paṭisevanā pahātabbā te paṭisevanāya pahīnā honti, "
msgstr ""
"By using, they’ve given up the defilements that should be given up by using. "

msgctxt "an6.58:2.4"
msgid "ye āsavā adhivāsanā pahātabbā te adhivāsanāya pahīnā honti, "
msgstr ""
"By enduring, they’ve given up the defilements that should be given up by "
"enduring. "

msgctxt "an6.58:2.5"
msgid "ye āsavā parivajjanā pahātabbā te parivajjanāya pahīnā honti, "
msgstr ""
"By avoiding, they’ve given up the defilements that should be given up by "
"avoiding. "

msgctxt "an6.58:2.6"
msgid "ye āsavā vinodanā pahātabbā te vinodanāya pahīnā honti, "
msgstr ""
"By getting rid, they’ve given up the defilements that should be given up by "
"getting rid. "

msgctxt "an6.58:2.7"
msgid "ye āsavā bhāvanā pahātabbā te bhāvanāya pahīnā honti."
msgstr ""
"By developing, they’ve given up the defilements that should be given up by "
"developing."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.388"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:3.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā saṃvarā pahātabbā ye saṃvarena pahīnā honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by restraint?"

msgctxt "an6.58:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso cakkhundriyasaṃvarasaṃvuto "
"viharati."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, lives restraining the eye faculty."

msgctxt "an6.58:3.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, cakkhundriyasaṃvaraṃ asaṃvutassa viharato uppajjeyyuṃ "
"āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, cakkhundriyasaṃvaraṃ saṃvutassa viharato evaṃsa te "
"āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without restraint of the eye faculty do not arise when there is such "
"restraint."

msgctxt "an6.58:3.4"
msgid "Paṭisaṅkhā yoniso sotindriya … pe …"
msgstr "Reflecting properly, they live restraining the ear faculty …"

msgctxt "an6.58:3.5"
msgid "ghānindriya …"
msgstr "the nose faculty …"

msgctxt "an6.58:3.6"
msgid "jivhindriya …"
msgstr "the tongue faculty …"

msgctxt "an6.58:3.7"
msgid "kāyindriya …"
msgstr "the body faculty …"

msgctxt "an6.58:3.8"
msgid "manindriyasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati."
msgstr "the mind faculty."

msgctxt "an6.58:3.9"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, manindriyasaṃvaraṃ asaṃvutassa viharato uppajjeyyuṃ "
"āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, manindriyasaṃvaraṃ saṃvutassa viharato evaṃsa te "
"āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without restraint of the mind faculty do not arise when there is such "
"restraint."

msgctxt "an6.58:3.10"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā saṃvarā pahātabbā ye saṃvarena pahīnā honti. "
"(1)"
msgstr "These are called the defilements that should be given up by restraint."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.389"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:4.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā paṭisevanā pahātabbā ye paṭisevanāya pahīnā "
"honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by using?"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso cīvaraṃ paṭisevati:"
msgstr "Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, makes use of robes:"

#. VAR: ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ → ḍaṃsa … siriṃsapasamphassānaṃ (bj, s1-3, km pī)
msgctxt "an6.58:4.3"
msgid ""
"‘yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, "
"ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva "
"hirikopīnapaṭicchādanatthaṃ’."
msgstr ""
"‘Only for the sake of warding off cold and heat; for warding off the touch "
"of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; and for covering the private "
"parts.’"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.4"
msgid "Paṭisaṅkhā yoniso piṇḍapātaṃ paṭisevati:"
msgstr "Reflecting properly, they make use of almsfood:"

#. VAR: phāsuvihāro ca → phāsuvihāro cāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an6.58:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘neva davāya na madāya na maṇḍanāya na vibhūsanāya, yāvadeva imassa kāyassa "
"ṭhitiyā yāpanāya, vihiṃsūparatiyā brahmacariyānuggahāya, iti purāṇañca "
"vedanaṃ paṭihaṅkhāmi, navañca vedanaṃ na uppādessāmi, yātrā ca me bhavissati "
"anavajjatā ca phāsuvihāro ca’."
msgstr ""
"‘Not for fun, indulgence, adornment, or decoration, but only to continue and "
"sustain this body, avoid harm, and support spiritual practice. So that I "
"will put an end to old discomfort and not give rise to new discomfort, and "
"so that I will keep on living blamelessly and at ease.’"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.6"
msgid "Paṭisaṅkhā yoniso senāsanaṃ paṭisevati:"
msgstr "Reflecting properly, they make use of lodgings:"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘yāvadeva sītassa paṭighātāya, uṇhassa paṭighātāya, "
"ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ paṭighātāya, yāvadeva "
"utuparissayavinodanapaṭisallānārāmatthaṃ’."
msgstr ""
"‘Only for the sake of warding off cold and heat; for warding off the touch "
"of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles; and to shelter from harsh "
"weather and enjoy retreat.’"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.8"
msgid "Paṭisaṅkhā yoniso gilānapaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paṭisevati:"
msgstr ""
"Reflecting properly, they make use of medicines and supplies for the sick:"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.9"
msgid ""
"‘yāvadeva uppannānaṃ veyyābādhikānaṃ vedanānaṃ paṭighātāya, "
"abyābajjhaparamatāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Only for the sake of warding off the pains of illness and to promote good "
"health.’"

msgctxt "an6.58:4.10"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, appaṭisevato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, "
"paṭisevato evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without using these things do not arise when they are used."

msgctxt "an6.58:4.11"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā paṭisevanā pahātabbā ye paṭisevanāya pahīnā "
"honti. (2)"
msgstr "These are called the defilements that should be given up by using."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:5.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā adhivāsanā pahātabbā ye adhivāsanāya pahīnā "
"honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by enduring?"

msgctxt "an6.58:5.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa, "
"jighacchāya, pipāsāya, ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ, duruttānaṃ "
"durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ, uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ "
"tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko "
"hoti."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, endures cold, heat, hunger, and "
"thirst. They endure the touch of flies, mosquitoes, wind, sun, and reptiles. "
"They endure rude and unwelcome criticism. And they put up with physical pain—"
"sharp, severe, acute, unpleasant, disagreeable, and life-threatening."

msgctxt "an6.58:5.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, anadhivāsato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, "
"adhivāsato evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without enduring these things do not arise when they are endured."

msgctxt "an6.58:5.4"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā adhivāsanā pahātabbā ye adhivāsanāya pahīnā "
"honti. (3)"
msgstr "These are called the defilements that should be given up by enduring."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.390"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:6.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā parivajjanā pahātabbā ye parivajjanāya pahīnā "
"honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by avoiding?"

msgctxt "an6.58:6.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso caṇḍaṃ hatthiṃ parivajjeti, "
"caṇḍaṃ assaṃ parivajjeti, caṇḍaṃ goṇaṃ parivajjeti, caṇḍaṃ kukkuraṃ "
"parivajjeti, ahiṃ khāṇuṃ kaṇṭakaṭṭhānaṃ sobbhaṃ papātaṃ candanikaṃ "
"oḷigallaṃ, yathārūpe anāsane nisinnaṃ, yathārūpe agocare carantaṃ, yathārūpe "
"pāpake mitte bhajantaṃ viññū sabrahmacārī pāpakesu ṭhānesu okappeyyuṃ, so "
"tañca anāsanaṃ tañca agocaraṃ te ca pāpake mitte paṭisaṅkhā yoniso "
"parivajjeti."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, avoids a wild elephant, a wild "
"horse, a wild ox, a wild dog, a snake, a stump, thorny ground, a pit, a "
"cliff, a swamp, and a sewer. Reflecting properly, they avoid sitting on "
"inappropriate seats, walking in inappropriate neighborhoods, and mixing with "
"bad friends—whatever sensible spiritual companions would believe to be a bad "
"setting."

msgctxt "an6.58:6.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, aparivajjayato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, "
"parivajjayato evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without avoiding these things do not arise when they are avoided."

msgctxt "an6.58:6.4"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā parivajjanā pahātabbā ye parivajjanāya pahīnā "
"honti. (4)"
msgstr "These are called the defilements that should be given up by avoiding."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:7.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā vinodanā pahātabbā ye vinodanāya pahīnā honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by getting rid?"

msgctxt "an6.58:7.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti "
"pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti, paṭisaṅkhā yoniso uppannaṃ "
"byāpādavitakkaṃ … uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale "
"dhamme nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, doesn’t tolerate a sensual, "
"malicious, or cruel thought that has arisen. They don’t tolerate any bad, "
"unskillful qualities that have arisen, but give them up, get rid of them, "
"eliminate them, and obliterated them."

msgctxt "an6.58:7.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, avinodayato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, "
"vinodayato evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without getting rid of these things do not arise when they are gotten "
"rid of."

msgctxt "an6.58:7.4"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā vinodanā pahātabbā ye vinodanāya pahīnā "
"honti. (5)"
msgstr ""
"These are called the defilements that should be given up by getting rid."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:8.1"
msgid ""
"Katame ca, bhikkhave, āsavā bhāvanā pahātabbā ye bhāvanāya pahīnā honti?"
msgstr "And what are the defilements that should be given up by developing?"

#. VAR: vosaggapariṇāmiṃ → vossagga … (bj, s1-3, pts1, c1)
msgctxt "an6.58:8.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu paṭisaṅkhā yoniso satisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti "
"vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vosaggapariṇāmiṃ, paṭisaṅkhā "
"yoniso dhammavicayasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … vīriyasambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
"pītisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … passaddhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … "
"samādhisambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti … upekkhāsambojjhaṅgaṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ "
"virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vosaggapariṇāmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who, reflecting properly, develops the awakening factors of "
"mindfulness, investigation of principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, "
"immersion, and equanimity, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and "
"cessation, and ripen as letting go."

msgctxt "an6.58:8.3"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ hissa, bhikkhave, abhāvayato uppajjeyyuṃ āsavā vighātapariḷāhā, "
"bhāvayato evaṃsa te āsavā vighātapariḷāhā na honti."
msgstr ""
"For the distressing and feverish defilements that might arise in someone who "
"lives without developing these things do not arise when they are developed."

msgctxt "an6.58:8.4"
msgid ""
"Ime vuccanti, bhikkhave, āsavā bhāvanā pahātabbā ye bhāvanāya pahīnā honti. "
"(6)"
msgstr "These are called the defilements that should be given up by developing."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an6.58:9.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, chahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti "
"pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant with these six factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the "
"gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a teacher’s offering, worthy of "
"veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the "
"world.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.58:9.2"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
